The '''Roadhouse Blues Tour''' was a 1970 tour undertaken by [[Rock music|rock]] band the [[The Doors|Doors]]. The group recorded many of the concerts which have been subsequently released through [[Elektra Records]], [[Rhino Records]] and Bright Midnight Records.
Concerts on the tour included: *[[Boston Arena]] in [[Boston]] April 10, 1970 *[[Neal S. Blaisdell Center|Honolulu International Centre]] in [[Honolulu]] April 18, 1970 *[[Spectrum (arena)|Spectrum]] in [[Philadelphia]] May 1, 1070 *[[Pittsburgh Civic Arena]] in [[Pittsburgh]] May 2, 1970 *[[Cobo Arena]] in [[Detroit]] May 8, 1970 *[[Seattle Center Coliseum]] in [[Seattle]] June 5, 1970 *[[Pacific Coliseum]] in [[Vancouver]] June 6, 1970 *[[Live at The Isle of Wight Festival 1970 (The Doors)|Isle of Wight Festival]] in the UK, August 29, 1970 *[[Music Hall at Fair Park]] in [[Dallas]] December 11, 1970 last officially recorded concert, and *The Warehouse in [[New Orleans]] December 12, 1970 the last Doors' concert featuring singer [[Jim Morrison]]
