[[File:Arriaga elurtua.jpg|260px|thumbnail|The building]] The '''Arriaga antzokia''' in Basque or '''Teatro Arriaga''' in Spanish is an [[opera house]] in [[Bilbao]], [[Spain]]. It was built in [[Neo-baroque]] style by architect [[Joaquín Rucoba]] in 1890, the same architect that built the [[Bilbao City Hall|city hall]]. It is named after [[Juan Crisóstomo Arriaga|Juan Crisóstomo de Arriaga]], known in his time as the "Spanish Mozart".
The theater was rebuilt in 1985 after severe flooding destroyed it in August 1983.
