'''Top Fest''' is a [[music competition]] organised by [[Top Channel]]. It began airing in 2004 and has been held since. It is annually held in [[Tirana]], [[Albania]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Fest|url=http://www.nix-music.tv/index.php/top-fest/|publisher=nix-music.tv|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011122039/http://www.nix-music.tv/index.php/top-fest|archivedate=2013-10-11|df=}}</ref> The songs are usually performed in [[Albanian language|Albanian]] with artists from Albania, [[Republic of Kosovo|Kosovo]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] and other Albanian-speaking territories. From its 7th edition (2010), the participants perform their entries 100% live.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Fest Awards|url=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL2E2B4E7287FCB35B}}</ref>
==Format== Since 2010, the show has been split into three phases. The first phase airs all accepted entries, performing their entries in playback. The second phase is the ''Semi-Finals'', usually split in three shows, where the winners from phase one perform. The qualifiers from the semi-finals perform in the final, usually 10 to 13 acts. The winner is chosen in the Finale-night, usually held in late-May or early-June.
===Winners=== The contest has produced many artists, like [[Alban Skënderaj]], [[Elhaida Dani]], and many others, who were established and rose fame after their participation in Top Fest.<ref>{{cite web|title=Samanta Karavello fiton "Top Fest 10"|url=http://gazeta-shqip.com/lajme/2013/06/09/samanta-karavello-fiton-top-fest-10-2/|publisher=Shqip|accessdate=9 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title="Top Fest 8", fiton Elvana Gjata me këngën kushtuar "Emmy"-t|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/2011/06/07/%E2%80%9Ctop-fest-8%E2%80%9D-fiton-elvana-gjata-me-kengen-kushtuar-%E2%80%9Cemmy%E2%80%9D-t/|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014045012/http://www.panorama.com.al/2011/06/07/%E2%80%9Ctop-fest-8%E2%80%9D-fiton-elvana-gjata-me-kengen-kushtuar-%E2%80%9Cemmy%E2%80%9D-t/|archivedate=2013-10-14|df=}}</ref>
